Germany’s Westerwelle to Seek Confidence Vote, Rheinische Says

-- B y   R a i n e r   B u e r g i n
-- 
2011-08-30T07:25:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-30/germany-s-westerwelle-to-seek-confidence-vote-rheinische-says.html
German Foreign Minister  Guido Westerwelle  will ask for a confidence vote at today’s meeting of
lawmakers from his Free Democratic Party, the  Rheinische Post 
 reported , citing unnamed people close to Westerwelle.  Westerwelle will seek a clear decision whether his party
wants him to keep his job after attracting criticism over
refusing to back military force by the North Atlantic Treaty
Organization against the government of Libyan leader Muammar Qaddafi, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Rainer Buergin in Berlin at 
 rbuergin1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Hertling at   jhertling@bloomberg.net  